μακαρίᾳ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[μ]νήμῃ \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γρηγώριος υἱὸς Πο\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γρηγώριος\">Γρηγώριος\u003C/span> υἱὸς \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πο\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πο\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Πο\">Πο\u003C/span>-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span> του π\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ρ\u003C/span>(εσ)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">β\u003C/span>(υτέρου) ζήσας ἔτη κβ´ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[τ(ελ)]ευτᾷ δὲ ἐν \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Κ\u003C/span>(υρί)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ῳ\u003C/span> μηνὴ Ἰ\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ου\u003C/span>(λίῳ) \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ἰν\u003Cspan class=\"intraline\" title=\"line through\">δ\u003C/span>(ικτιῶνος) η´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":104,"ptr":105,"ref":107,"inscriptionDate":4,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6,"year":4},"92 n.20",{"target":106},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/6KPB9V5B",{"_":108,"target":108},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001787",2006,{"file":111,"uri":111,"title":112,"status":113,"editionAuthor":115,"type":116,"objectType":117,"material":118,"condition":73,"layoutDesc":123,"handNote":127,"date":208,"places":213,"geo":221,"country":63,"provenance":215,"provenanceGeo":225,"region":67,"settlement":215,"repository":228,"idno":232,"textLang":235,"tmNumber":237,"facsimile":238,"letterHeights":245,"publications":283,"zotero":286,"keywords":289,"html":297,"bibl":298,"bulletinDateSort":109,"citedRangeSort":301,"languageSort":75,"materialSort":119,"typeSort":21},"ISic003337","Funerary inscription for Eirena",{"_":114},"edited",null,{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"_":25,"ana":26,"ref":27},{"_":119,"ana":120,"type":31,"subtype":121,"resp":122,"ref":33},"Very fine-grained, veined, white marble, likely Pavonazzetto, Docimian. Digital microscopy: indistinguishable fabric. Scribbly veins, maybe a limestone (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy)","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.Pavonazzetto #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Docimian","Pavonazzetto|Docimian","#Coccato",{"layout":124},{"p":125,"rs":126,"damage":73},"Ten lines of Greek filling the available space, decreasing notably in size in the second five lines",{"_":40,"ana":41,"ref":42},{"lettering":128,"dimensions":129},"The letters are engraved in a fairly plain, square fashion, with simple serifs. Alpha is mostly with broken bar, sometimes with an extended upper serif, although there is a straight bar example in line 7 and in lines 8 and 10 straight bar descending to left foot; beta is closed, with larger lower eye, generally horizontal along the base; delta varies between regular triangle and oblique lower bar with extended serif above; epsilon has straight bars of equal length, except for instances in lines 9 and 10 when it is lunate; theta is ovoid with connecting straight bar; kappa has short tails; lambda sometimes has an extended upper serif; mu varies between a form with vertical first and last hastae and short middle strokes meeting above the line and cursive form comparable to a lower-case mu in line 9; omicron is full size in the first few lines, but increasingly is smaller and mid-line; sigma is consistently lunate, but more often formed of three straight strokes; less often a single curved stroke; omega is consistently lunate, and sometimes smaller and mid-line. The eta and nu are in ligature in lines 5, 6 and 7. In line 5 the omicron in the final word is inscribed above the other letters (due to omission?). The last two/three words of the last line are enclosed between a pair of christograms. Small hedera occur in lines 1, 3, 5, and 10.",[130,134,139,144,149,152,158,163,168,173,179,182,186,189,193,197,199,203,206],{"type":49,"l":50,"from":51,"to":51,"h":131,"unit":52,"atLeast":132,"atMost":133},"12-18","12","18",{"type":49,"l":135,"from":56,"to":56,"h":136,"unit":52,"atLeast":137,"atMost":138},"Line 2","14-19","14","19",{"type":49,"l":140,"from":141,"to":141,"h":142,"unit":52,"atLeast":132,"atMost":143},"Line 3","line3","12-22","22",{"type":49,"l":145,"from":146,"to":146,"h":147,"unit":52,"atLeast":148,"atMost":143},"Line 4","line4","8-22","8",{"type":49,"l":150,"from":151,"to":151,"h":131,"unit":52,"atLeast":132,"atMost":133},"Line 5","line5",{"type":49,"l":153,"from":154,"to":154,"h":155,"unit":52,"atLeast":156,"atMost":157},"Line 6","line6","9-16","9","16",{"type":49,"l":159,"from":160,"to":160,"h":161,"unit":52,"atLeast":162,"atMost":137},"Line 7","line7","7-14","7",{"type":49,"l":164,"from":165,"to":165,"h":166,"unit":52,"atLeast":167,"atMost":132},"Line 8","line8","6-12","6",{"type":49,"l":169,"from":170,"to":170,"h":171,"unit":52,"atLeast":167,"atMost":172},"Line 9","line9","6-10","10",{"type":49,"l":174,"from":175,"to":175,"h":176,"unit":52,"atLeast":177,"atMost":178},"Line 10","line10","5-13","5","13",{"type":54,"l":55,"from":51,"to":56,"h":180,"unit":52,"atLeast":172,"atMost":181},"10-15","15",{"type":54,"l":183,"from":56,"to":141,"h":184,"unit":52,"atLeast":185,"atMost":162},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","3-7","3",{"type":54,"l":187,"from":141,"to":146,"h":188,"unit":52,"atLeast":177,"atMost":181},"Interlineation line 3 to 4","5-15",{"type":54,"l":190,"from":146,"to":151,"h":191,"unit":52,"atLeast":192,"atMost":172},"Interlineation line 4 to 5","4-10","4",{"type":54,"l":194,"from":151,"to":154,"h":195,"unit":52,"atLeast":196,"atMost":162},"Interlineation line 5 to 6","2-7","2",{"type":54,"l":198,"from":154,"to":160,"h":195,"unit":52,"atLeast":196,"atMost":162},"Interlineation line 6 to 7",{"type":54,"l":200,"from":160,"to":165,"h":201,"unit":52,"atLeast":202,"atMost":167},"Interlineation line 7 to 8","1-6","1",{"type":54,"l":204,"from":165,"to":170,"h":205,"unit":52,"atLeast":202,"atMost":177},"Interlineation line 8 to 9","1-5",{"type":54,"l":207,"from":170,"to":175,"h":205,"unit":52,"atLeast":202,"atMost":177},"Interlineation line 9 to 10",{"_":209,"notBefore":210,"notAfter":211,"evidence":212},"5th century CE, with a likely terminus post quem of 403-408 CE, given that a coin of that date was found within the tomb (Tigano 2009: 164; more generally, the tombs of this part of the necropolis all date late 4th to 5th century CE)",403,500,"archaeological-context",[214,217],{"_":215,"type":64,"ref":216,"region":63},"Halaesa","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":218,"type":68,"ref":219,"offset":220,"region":63},"Castel di Tusa","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[222],[223,224],37.99907,14.26197,[226,227],38.0073241,14.2527381,{"_":229,"role":230,"ref":231},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":233,"type":234},"ME 20272","inventory",{"_":75,"mainLang":76,"languages":236},[75],"645584",{"n":239,"url":240,"height":241,"width":242,"desc":243,"surfaceType":244},"screen","ISic003337_tiled.tif","3387px","5310px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina","front",[246,249,252,254,256,257,260,262,264,266,269,271,273,274,276,278,279,281,282],{"atLeast":247,"atMost":248},12,18,{"atLeast":250,"atMost":251},14,19,{"atLeast":247,"atMost":253},22,{"atLeast":255,"atMost":253},8,{"atLeast":247,"atMost":248},{"atLeast":258,"atMost":259},9,16,{"atLeast":261,"atMost":250},7,{"atLeast":263,"atMost":247},6,{"atLeast":263,"atMost":2